	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Paste markdown templates (including images) into note.com editor.

Configuration (Alfred Preferences > Workflows > Configure Workflow):
- Use uv if available (NOTE_USE_UV): checked by default.
  Requires uv (https://astral.sh/uv). Uncheck to use system Python instead
  (requires: pip3 install pyobjc-framework-Cocoa).
- Templates Directory (NOTE_TEMPLATES_DIR): path to your .md templates folder
  (default: ~/Documents/Note Templates).

Usage:
1. Create .md files in your templates folder using standard markdown image syntax:
   ![caption](./images/photo.png)
2. Open note.com editor in your browser
3. Trigger Alfred with keyword "note", select a template, press Enter</string>
